page.title: 15TREVAYLOR WOODS.
page.content:
In Trevaylor woods there are beech, oak,sycamore,pines and rhododendrons. These were planted in Victorian times; they grow beside the stream and in-amongst the trees.As well as rhododendrons there are bluebells. There are lots of animals and birds and plenty of homes in the woods for them.There are vandals who go into the woods at night and chop down small trees and saplings for firewood. The majority of saplings are{beech,}which are protected by plastic tubes around them.In the woods there is a stream called Trevaylor stream which runs through the woods and into Gulval. The woods are nice and cool om a hot day. The woods grow on the land of Rosemorran Farm, Gulval. The woods are quiet and shady.
Alv.
